20. An intramedullary medical device, comprising:
a sleeve comprising:
a closed end;
an insertion tip connected to the closed end;
wherein the insertion tip includes a first through-hole adapted to receive a first bone anchor;
a shape memory alloy element attached to a first interior surface of the sleeve;
an anchor element attached to the shape memory alloy element, the anchor element comprising a second through-hole adapted to receive a second bone anchor; and
wherein the anchor element and the sleeve are slidably interconnected.

27. An intramedullary medical device, comprising:
a proximal anchor element adapted to be fixed to a human tibia;
a shape memory alloy element connected with the proximal anchor element; and
a distal anchor element connected with shape memory alloy element, wherein the distal anchor element is adapted to be fixed to a human calcaneus;
wherein the distal anchor element is slidably interconnected with the proximal anchor element.

claim.claim-text:
The medical device (200) of claim 1, wherein the distal anchor element has a distal bone screw interface disposed within the rigid element;
(ii) wherein the rigid element includes an access port positioned outside the distal bone screw interface;
(iii) wherein the access port is adapted such that the distal bone screw interface may be accessed in configurations of the non-linear contracting element having the pseudo-elastic range of expansive strain; and
(iv) wherein the non-linear contracting element is adapted such that the pseudo-elastic range of expansive strain provides through the rigid element compressive forces between the at least two bone pieces.
